HEADWORD: Court-leet
<hw>Court"-leet`</hw> <pr>(-l?t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A court of record held once a year, in a particular hundred, lordship, or manor, before the steward of the leet.</def>  <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

